Commands for Specific File-types (F10-F12)
******************************************

With the exception of unmodified F10, function keys F10-F12 are mostly
reserved for functions that are specific to the particular type of
file being edited.  If nothing else is defined for a particular
file-type, the default is that F12 compiles and F11 runs.  Note also
that for some types of files, Shft-F1 produces context-sensitive help.

F10 on its own is the key that allows you to navigate the menus with
the keyboard; but note that this does not yet work under GTK for
GNU/Linux.

